<TITLE> Violence shuts NUST </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Noakhali, June 23 (bdnews24.com) -- Noakhali University of Science and Technology (NUST) has been closed indefinitely since Saturday following a seven-day continuous movement by students demanding withdrawal of increased fees. At about 11.30 pm Friday, police rescued four teachers whom the students had kept confined. The university authorities asked the students to vacate the halls and campus by 8am, but they did not leave until 11.30am. The students alleged that eight of their fellows including Dipu, Angel, Kabir and Akash had been injured in police action at the hall Friday night. The vice chancellor of the University Dr Abul Khair said that the university had been closed sine die, and students ordered to vacate the halls to bring the situation under control. Tension was prevailing on campus when the latest report arrived. The latest incident brings to two the number of universities closed in the country in four days. Ahsanullah University of Science and Technology in the capital has also been closed since Wednesday following agitation by students demanding shifting of educational activities to the permanent campus. Students of the private university alleged that the authorities had been dillydallying since long in shifting academic activities to its permanent building at Tejgaon from its temporary campus at 20 Tejturi Bazar. When the students demanded a deadline for shifting the University, the authorities closed it without any discussion. bdnews24.c
